"Quadratus femoris","Piriformis","Gluteus maximus"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Egluteus maximus\u003C/strong\u003E is the major extensor of the hip joint and plays a crucial role in stabilising the knee joint through its insertion into the iliotibial band. It is also important for external rotation, abduction, and stabilisation of the hip.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPiriformis\u003C/strong\u003E - Primarily involved in external rotation of the hip\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIliopsoas\u003C/strong\u003E - Major flexor of the hip joint\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EQuadratus femoris\u003C/strong\u003E - Involved in external rotation of the hip\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObturator internus\u003C/strong\u003E - Also involved in external rotation of the hip\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The gluteus maximus is the major extensor of the hip joint.","The gluteus maximus stabilises the knee joint through its insertion into the iliotibial band.","The gluteus maximus is involved in external rotation and abduction of the hip."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2018). Textbook of Orthopaedics, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Singh, V. (2018). Textbook of Anatomy Abdomen and Lower Limb; Volume II (Vol. 2). Elsevier Health Sciences","Cantrell AJ, Imonugo O, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Leg Bones. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537024/","Raftery A. General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System. Ann R Coll Surg Engl. 2006 Jul;88(4):425. doi: 10.1308/003588406X114802d. PMCID: PMC1964629","Chaudhry SR, Nahian A, Chaudhry K. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis, Pelvis. [Updat